&lt;p&gt;Reports to: Lead Operator Stratospheric Systems&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: Nationwide with candidates residing within 60-90 minutes’ drive time of a major airport.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Status: Full-time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pay Range: $17 - $20/hr&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Travel: 100% travel role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Near Space Labs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Near Space Labs is leading the next generation of Earth imaging. We design, build, and operate a fleet of proprietary, stratospheric systems called Swiftys. Our Swiftys fly to the edge of space to deliver high quality, updated imagery of our planet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flight Operations is a fast-paced growing organization responsible for operating and launching our fleet of Swiftys throughout the U.S. to meet our customer imaging and data needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of a three person Pod (team) responsible for launching image capturing stratospheric systems around the USA.&amp;nbsp; The Associate Operator Stratospheric Systems plays a critical role in executing and scaling our flight operational footprint.&amp;nbsp; The incumbent will operate, maintain, and fly our fleet of Swiftys throughout the nation. The incumbent will collaborate and communicate within the Pod. The Associate Operator Stratospheric Systems will troubleshoot and provide maintenance on the technical hardware. The incumbent will perform work outdoors including hiking, walking and general physical duties throughout an extended workday.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Job Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the Lead Operator Stratospheric Systems,&amp;nbsp; and other Operators, occasional contractors, and Mission Control, to ensure Swiftys are launched, maintained, and recovered effectively, contributing to the overall success of the mission operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the maintain and operate our fleet of Swiftys ensuring consistent delivery of high-quality data to the Company’s customers, driving the success of our overall operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide information and feedback in the generation of failure reports for malfunctions and abnormalities in the Swifty and associated equipment through our data tracking tool.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the daily technical reports of work performed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strictly follow Near Space Labs operational, safety and manufacturing procedures and processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work under the direction of the Lead Operator Stratospheric Systems or Operators to ensure successful mission execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in daily debriefs to summarize and plan field operations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to improvements feedback to Near Space Labs operational procedures and processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the Swifty and operations metrics for the field through technical reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely drive and maintain our fleet of road launch vehicles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Additional Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrates a high degree of professionalism in communication, attitude, and teamwork.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrates a high level of work quality, attendance, and appearance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to all Company policies, procedures, and safety regulations.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adhere to local, state, and federal laws.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Additional responsibilities assigned by supervisor related to your position and or department.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work long varied hours, nights, days, and weekends to support business needs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working Schedule:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work a 15 day

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a growth-stage technology company at the forefront of geospatial imaging. We provide high-fidelity, actionable spatial data and analytics that empower our clients to make critical, real-world decisions. As we scale our market presence, we are looking for driven, agile professionals to help us build the foundation for exponential revenue growth.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Near Space Labs operates the world&#39;s largest stratospheric imaging and data capture platform. We launch our proprietary, autonomous vehicles robots to altitudes between 60,000 and 100,000 feet. From this vantage point, we capture petabytes of high-resolution aerial imagery and data to support business, community, and climate resilience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Director of Marketing&lt;/strong&gt; to serve as the central engine of our marketing organization. In this high-impact role, you will operate as an elite solo marketer with the strategic acumen to partner with both internal stakeholders and external agencies to drive successful outcomes. This is a hands-on leadership opportunity designed for a builder who will own the strategy, establish the systems, and drive execution from the ground up.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will spearhead modern B2B digital marketing initiatives to accelerate top-of-funnel pipeline and lead product marketing across diverse verticals: &lt;strong&gt;Insurance, State &amp;amp; Local Government, Energy &amp;amp; Utilities, MapTech, Forestry &amp;amp; Environment, Roofing &amp;amp; Home Services, and Architecture, Engineering &amp;amp; Construction (AEC)&lt;/strong&gt;. As a vital partner to Sales, Product, and the Executive team, you must demonstrate exceptional adaptability and a startup mentality — navigating context switching with ease.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reporting to:&lt;/strong&gt; Chief Revenue Officer (CRO)&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; Hybrid in Brooklyn, NY&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Employment Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-Time&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Demand Generation &amp;amp; Top-of-Funnel: &lt;/strong&gt;Own digital marketing strategy to drive qualified pipeline: paid, SEO/content, email, and ABM. Build scalable programs that generate awareness and inbound interest across our target verticals — insurance, utilities, infrastructure, and beyond.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Marketing &amp;amp; Sales Enablement: &lt;/strong&gt;Develop and maintain messaging frameworks, positioning, and collateral tailored to multiple distinct buyer personas and use cases. Partner with Product and Sales to translate complex geospatial technology into stories that close deals and expand accounts — including vertical-specific decks, one-pagers, battlecards, and ROI narratives.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brand &amp;amp; Thought Leadership: &lt;/strong&gt;Shape the Near Space Labs brand across owned and earned channels. Define our voice, narrative, and visual identity. Build a robust thought leadership program — including bylined articles, speaking opportunities, and executive content — that positions Near Space Labs as the definitive voice in stratospheric intelligence. Oversee the broader content calendar: case studies, technical explainers, and industry commentary, working with agencies or freelancers to execute at scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agency &amp;amp; Vendor Management: &lt;/strong&gt;Identify, brief, and manage external agencies and contractors for execution support across design, paid media, content, PR, and events — maintaining quality and staying on budget.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Events &amp;amp; Field Marketing: &lt;/strong&gt;Own conference strategy and field presence

&lt;p&gt;At Near Space Labs we design, build and operate a fleet of stratospheric robots to image the earth. We launch our proprietary, balloon-based imaging robots to heights between 40,000 and 60,000 feet. From this vantage point, we capture petabytes of imagery for a variety of use cases. Our mission is to provide high quality, updated imagery that we believe should be accessible to everyone who needs it. By approaching earth imaging from a new vantage point and applying cutting edge methodologies, we drive faster aerospace innovation without tradeoffs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are always on the look out for creative, curious, and diverse problem solvers who thrive in organized chaos. If you’re a hardworking innovative thinker who is passionate about pushing boundaries in the aerospace field and contributing to a collaborative environment, then we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locations&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brooklyn, NY / US (remote)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barcelona, Spain / EU nationals or work permit holders&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;General Skills We Look For:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Not all of this is required&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Business, Data Science, Management Information Systems or a related analytical field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Data Analytics, Computer Science, Information Systems, Business Administration, or a related field, or equivalent professional experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;3+ years of experience working with technical hardware, or a BS degree desirable but not essential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in an engineering production or maintenance organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proven track record of 2-5 years in a relevant field, demonstrating expertise and experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience in managing teams, effectively delegating tasks, and optimizing operational workflows to achieve desired outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously, prioritize tasks effectively, and ensure adherence to strict deadlines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A solid background in workflow coordination, efficient task assignment, and the implementation of robust quality assurance processes, preferably within a data-intensive environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to review processing performance metrics, identify trends, and suggest data-informed improvements to existing workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity in using workflow management tools such as Airtable or similar platforms for effective task tracking and team collaboration is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Geospatial/Remote Sensing Experience (nice to have)&lt;strong&gt;:&lt;/strong&gt; Familiarity with aerial imagery, mapping principles, or Geographic Information Systems (GIS) is advantageous but not a prerequisite.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Don&#39;t Meet Every Requirement?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Studies have shown that women, marginalized genders, and people of color are less likely to apply to jobs unless they meet every single qualification. At Near Space Labs, we are dedicated to building a diverse, inclusive, and authentic workplace, so if you’re excited about applying but your past experience doesn’t align perfectly with every qualification in the general skills listed, then we encourage you to apply anyways. You may be just the right candidate for this or other roles.&lt;/p&gt;
